    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "This is related to https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/issues/1716, where it was brought up that a header on the source should not be taken as any sort of guarantee of security. A hint to where the code comes from does sound like a good idea however.\r\n\r\nRegarding implementation, this would be done as a new script in `scripts/release`, called from [version.sh](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/master/scripts/release/version.sh) (see [synchronize-versions.js](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/master/scripts/release/synchronize-versions.js) for a similar one).",
